704133f-a.title: Brooklyn: Emmons Avenue - Coyle Street
704133f-a.text:
Emmons Ave., south side, opposite Coyle Street, showing Beau Rivage,
owned by Gulotti and Vannini in 1922 and by W.E. Morson and Popper in 1925.
December 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

704132f-a.title: Brooklyn: Emmons Avenue - Coyle Street
704132f-a.text:
Emmons Ave., east from Coyle to Bragg Streets, showing the Plumb Beach
Casino, demolished about 1928, which was the dancing and dining establishment
for the bathers and picnickers in this area.
DDecember 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
